===Languages===
{{Main|Languages of Afghanistan}}
[[File:Afghan Schoolchildren in Kabul.jpg|thumb|Most Afghans are bilingual.]]
The two [[official language]]s of Afghanistan are [[Pashto]] (since 1936) and [[Dari Persian]] (since 1964). Both are [[Indo-European languages]] from the [[Iranian languages]] sub-family.&lt;ref name=&quot;CAL-lang&quot;&gt;{{cite web |url=http://www.cal.org/co/afghan/alang.html |title=The Afghans - Language and Literacy |work=Barbara Robson and Juliene Lipson, with assistance from Farid Younos and Mariam Mehdi |accessdate=2010-09-16|publisher=[[Center for Applied Linguistics]] |location=United States|date=June 30, 2002}}&lt;/ref&gt; Persian has always been the [[Prestige (sociolinguistics)|prestige language]] and as the main means of inter-ethnic communication it has maintained its status of [[lingua franca]]. Persian is the native tongue of various Afghan ethnic groups including the [[Tajik people|Tajik]]s, Afghanistan's second largest ethnic group, the [[Hazara people|Hazara]], [[Aimak]] and Kizilbash.&lt;ref name=&quot;Encyclopaedia Britannica&quot;&gt;{{cite web |url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/7798/Afghanistan/226122/Languages |title=Languages of Afghanistan|work=|accessdate=|publisher=[[Encyclopaedia Britannica]] |location=|date=}}&lt;/ref&gt; Pashto is the native tongue of the [[Pashtuns]], the single largest ethno-linguistic group within Afghanistan. Other languages, such as [[Uzbek language|Uzbek]], [[Arabic language|Arabic]], [[Turkmen language|Turkmen]], [[Balochi language|Balochi]], [[Pashayi language|Pashayi]] and [[Nuristani languages]] ([[Askunu language|Ashkunu]], [[Kamkata-viri language|Kamkata-viri]], [[Vasi-vari language|Vasi-vari]], [[Tregami language|Tregami]] and [[Kalasha-ala language|Kalasha-ala]]), are used as native tongue by minority groups across the country and have official status in the regions where they are widely spoken. Minor languages also include [[Pamir languages|Pamiri]] ([[Shughni language|Shughni]], [[Munji language|Munji]], [[Ishkashimi language|Ishkashimi]] and [[Wakhi language|Wakhi]]), [[Brahui language|Brahui]], [[Hindko language|Hindko]], [[Kyrgyz language|Kyrgyz]], etc. A fair number of Afghans can also speak and understand [[Urdu]], [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]], [[Hindi]] and English.&lt;ref name=&quot;CAL-lang&quot;/&gt;

