|valign=&quot;top&quot;|The [[Government of India]] also considers Afghanistan to be a bordering country. This is because it considers the entire state of [[Jammu and Kashmir]] to be a part of India including the portion bordering Afghanistan. A ceasefire sponsored by the [[United Nations]] in 1948 froze the positions of Indian and Pakistani-held territory. As a consequence, the region bordering Afghanistan is in [[Pakistan-administered Kashmir]].
